@startuml
!include ../../styles/plantuml-theme.puml

top to bottom direction
title FIG-08-05. Horizon Bank payment data lineage

skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam nodesep 55
skinparam ranksep 55

rectangle "Horizon Digital Channels\n<<Originating application>>" as Digital #EAF6E8
rectangle "Payment instruction\ncustomer, debtor, creditor, amount" as Instruction #FFFFFF
rectangle "Payments Platform\n<<Transformation and orchestration>>" as Payments #EAF6E8
rectangle "Financial Crime Platform\n<<Screening use>>" as FinancialCrime #FFF4D6
rectangle "Core Deposit System\n<<Posting system>>" as Core #FFF4D6
rectangle "Screening request\npayment parties and amount" as ScreeningRequest #FFFFFF
rectangle "Screening result\nstatus and reason" as ScreeningResult #FFFFFF
rectangle "Posting request\naccepted payment instruction" as PostingRequest #FFFFFF
rectangle "Posting result\naccepted, rejected or pending" as Posting #FFFFFF
rectangle "Consolidated payment status event\ninstruction id, screening status, posting status" as Consolidated #FFFFFF
rectangle "Event Platform\n<<Distribution>>" as EventPlatform #F1E8FA
rectangle "Enterprise Data Platform\n<<Curated consumption>>" as DataPlatform #F2F5F7
rectangle "Payment data product\nreporting and control attributes" as DataProduct #FFFFFF

Digital --> Instruction : captures
Instruction --> Payments : submits
Payments -right-> ScreeningRequest
ScreeningRequest -right-> FinancialCrime
FinancialCrime -down-> ScreeningResult
Payments -right-> PostingRequest
PostingRequest -right-> Core
Core --> Posting
Payments --> Consolidated : original instruction context
ScreeningResult --> Consolidated
Posting --> Consolidated
Consolidated --> EventPlatform : consolidated payment status event
EventPlatform --> DataPlatform : payment status event stream
DataPlatform --> DataProduct : curates

note bottom
  Lineage view.
  It shows origin, screening and posting result inputs, consolidation and downstream use.
  It is not the BPMN payment repair process or a warehouse schema.
end note
@enduml
